sessions.title: Transform Banking with Google
sessions.description: Wellington Holbrook is leading ATB Financial through an intense three year business transformation with a big mandate, to reimagine banking and make it work for people. Keeping the customer at the center of every decision, Wellington will share his roadmap for this transformation success, which started with transitioning to GSuite and now include the full suite of powerful Google Cloud Platform products.

sessions.title: Mission Migration: Billions of Connections. Thousands of Dependencies. Migration in 3...2..1.
sessions.description:
Large scale enterprise migrations are challenging. With billions of connections and thousands of dependencies creating extreme complexity, migrations are one of the most difficult projects to execute successfully. 

How do you launch your migration successfully?

From discovery and application dependency identification through to Migration, in 45 minutes we'll cover how DATA can fuel your understanding, power optimization, and accelerate modernization and help you successfully navigate your cloud migration.

sessions.title: Supercharging your applications with Cloud Functions
sessions.description:
Cloud Functions for Firebase empowers web, mobile, and IoT developers to build simple, yet powerful backend features to their applications. I will be covering a quick intro into the what & why of Cloud Functions and finish up with some typical use-cases & examples of Cloud Functions for Firebase.

Have you ever started building an application and quickly realized that a lot of back-end work is needed? Cloud Functions is a serverless execution environment for building and connecting cloud services. With Cloud Functions you write simple, single-purpose functions that are attached to events emitted from your cloud infrastructure and services. There is no need to provision any infrastructure or worry about managing any servers.

In this session, you’ll see how using Cloud Functions for Firebase can help you quickly build out task heavy features for your web/mobile/IoT application as well as easily integrate with 3rd-party tools & services.

sessions.title: Drive Innovation: Reimagine Hybrid and Multi-Cloud Architecture with Anthos
sessions.description: A detailed walk through of why Anthos is important to you.

sessions.title: How UX makes GCP the Best Cloud for Developers
sessions.description:
User Experience (UX) is an incredibly important aspect of Google Cloud Platform.

In this panel we will give you an overview of UX research in Google Cloud Platform and provide example of how Google UX research and methodology translates into a more that provide meaningful and relevant experiences for developers.

sessions.title: To Infinity and Beyond... and Back Again.
sessions.description: A story of how our tech was formed, where it is headed and how it affects us as developers.

sessions.title: Kubernetes 101 in 3D
sessions.description: Introduction to Kubernetes with 3D animations

sessions.title: Google for Startups: Launch with Google
sessions.description: Learn how Google Cloud for Startups can help you launch.

sessions.title: Streaming Data Pipelines: Creating Next Gen Banking Analytics
sessions.description: Making banking work for people means evolving solutions to meet the demands of tomorrow. In this talk, we will discuss how Google Cloud Platform (GCP) can be used to find innovative ways in producing robust and cost-efficient real-time data processing and analysis. We will also illustrate how GCP can be leveraged to produce next gen banking analytic systems.

sessions.title: Updates from KubeCon + CloudNativeCon North America 2019
sessions.description: I will be visiting the KubeCon + CloudNativeCon North America 2019 in San Diego, California from November 18–21, 2019. I will also see if I can bring in more people who attended the conference to this devfest so that it would be a team of people sharing the experience and lessons learned

sessions.title: Machine Learning 101
sessions.description:
Artificial intelligence and machine learning (AI and ML) are major buzzwords right now. But as much as people are talking about AI, what does it actually mean for business? In ML 101, we'll answer this and more, including:

What exactly is AI/ML and why is it happening now?

Why is there an opportunity here in Alberta?

Where has AI/ML been applied successfully in industry?

And, most importantly: how can a company embark on an AI/ML strategy?

This will be a tech-free presentation. No jargon, just a basic look at artificial intelligence, machine learning and what they can do for business.

sessions.title: Deep Learning Fellowship Presents An Introduction to Deep Learning
sessions.description: In depth presentation of deep learning models and concepts with a focus on real world applications.

sessions.title: How Khan Academy Tracks Learning Time
sessions.description: Khan Academy is getting smarter about making its students smarter. We recently built a new real time data pipeline to track our students' learning time.  We use various Google Cloud products including GAE, Google Storage, BigQuery, Dataflow, StackDriver, and more.  Find out how we process thousands of learning events per second.

sessions.title: Local Businesses Leveraging Google My Business
sessions.description: Local business: Want to build business and grow awareness? Simple ways to use Google My Business platform to expose brands to more customers and sales!

sessions.title: InstaFly Me!
sessions.description: We will explore how www.instafly.me is leveraging machine learning to bring magic to travel booking.

sessions.title: Developer Student Clubs
sessions.description:
Developer Student Clubs are all over the Globe now.
What are they? What do they do? How can you get involved?

sessions.title: Building Scalable Oil and Gas Systems on GCP
sessions.description: We will walk through the architecture of how we used GCP in our Akinê Live Well Optimization platform.  Akinê Live is the platform we created to manage our IoT devices in the oil field.

sessions.title: Lunch
sessions.description: High quality, nutritious food.

sessions.title: Tips and Tricks for Finding Your Next Job
sessions.description: Some tips and ideas for helping new or stalled job-hunted based upon 30+ years of  experience

sessions.title: Empowering Business Users & Knowledge Workers with Google Cloud
sessions.description: Build what’s next together - regardless of your level of experience! Google Cloud has given business users and knowledge workers to be developers of custom applications and solutions that can solve their business problems. G-Suite in particular has enabled these citizen developers to build powerful solutions in Sheets, Forms and App Maker. In this session, I will cover how developers of different skill levels can utilize G-Suite and GCP to create awesome solutions.

sessions.title: Women Techmakers
sessions.description: Google's Women Techmakers program provides visibility, community, and resources for women in technology. Learn more about what the initiatives are, what WTM can provide, and how you can get involved.

sessions.title: Building Augmented Reality Applications
sessions.description:
-- Hands on session on how to get started with Unity.
-- Acquiring 3D assets.
-- Build AR/VR applications/games.
-- To get the most out of the session - pre-download Unity on your laptop (https://store.unity.com/download-nuo)
-- We are going to use Google Poly API for game asset management (https://poly.google.com/)

sessions.title: Get hands on with Flutter! Flutter 102, Layout Basics
sessions.description:
Flutter is taking the world by storm, enabling developers to write 90%+ of an app just once, then reuse that code to release to mobile, desktop and web.

Join us for Flutter 102, Layout Basics! Together we'll work through a customized workshop that was inspired by a layout tutorial designed by the Flutter team itself. When we're done, you'll know how easy it is to put together a great UI in Flutter!

So come get some hands-on experience with Flutter, and see how it can make your life a whole lot easier!

Please have Flutter installed and test that you can create a basic Flutter app before this workshop. We don't have enough time to walk people through installing Flutter and do the workshop too.

sessions.title: Doors Open + Light Breakfast
sessions.description: Get you spot for the keynote! Doors open at 8:00 AM

sessions.title: Keeping it Re(lation)al: moving from MySQL to Cloud Spanner without skipping a beat
sessions.description: At Quizlet, one of our highest throughput services, backed by MySQL, has been the source of multiple performance problems. In addition to the high throughput, the data managed by this service has a growth rate of ~2 billion records/month (and increasing!). At peak traffic, the service takes upwards of 10K writes/second. With scalability problems breathing down our neck, we decided to migrate our data and workload on to Cloud Spanner. There were challenges at every step of the way, from designing the schema, to migrating data, and getting a microservice serving from Cloud Spanner, without taking an outage. Did we succeed? What lessons did we learn along the way? Come find out.

sessions.title: Microservices at the Enterprise
sessions.description:
New to microservices within the Enterprise? Come learn some of the core concepts around Microservices and how to start to decouple away from your Enterprise monolithic application.

Core concepts of Enterprise Microservices include Designing Microservices, Service Communications, Data Management, Governance, Integrating Microservices  and the Service Mesh.

sessions.title: Flutter: State Management with Provider
sessions.description:
As of v1.8.2 the Flutter team strongly recommends using Provider for all state management solutions, large or small. This is straight from the horse's mouth, Chris Sells, Program Manager for Flutter.

Interestingly enough, the Flutter team released a package called "Package Provider" three days after Remi Rousselet released his package, "Provider". During the time each of these was developed, Remi had no idea the team was working on a solution and neither did the team know about Remi. But here's the twist in the plot...

When the team looked at both packages, they recommended Remi's version over their own. They so strongly recommend it that they announced to the world at Google I/O19 that Remi's is better, and people should use it.

Come find out why.

sessions.title: Flutter, why it's the right choice for business
sessions.description:
Let's cut the buzzwords. You don't care about phrases created by Marketing people, you care about what you could do with Flutter. You care if it's really that much faster and easier than what you're doing now, and if it's worth the time and expense it takes to get productive with it.

Come find out.

sessions.title: Closing Remarks
sessions.description: Closing Remarks, Thanks, Sponsors, Prizes

sessions.title: Actions on Google: Are you prepared for the next type of search?
sessions.description:
Voice is quickly becoming the new standard for search and most businesses are not ready for it. Using Actions on Google, developers are able to design, build, and distribute fully-customizable conversational applications.

Actions on Google is a developer platform that lets you create software to extend the functionality of the Google Assistant, Google’s virtual personal assistant, across more than 500 million devices, including smart speakers, phones, cars, TVs, headphones, watches, and much more.

In this session, you’ll learn the fundamentals needed for building Actions on Google, including Voice UI (VUI) & conversational design, what tools are available, some resources to get you started, and more!

sessions.title: Deep Learning Fellowship Presents Applications for Deep Learning Models
sessions.description: A review of deep learning models and their uses in the real world.

sessions.title: Untapped Energy's 2019 reClaim Data Competition - Closing Ceremony
sessions.description:
Untapped Energy is a not-for-profit, grassroots-led community with representation from industry, government, academia and the broader public, seeking to collectively solve problems and generate innovation for the Canadian energy industry using data science and analytics.

Throughout the month, Untapped Energy has run its 2019 reCLAIM Data Competition and we are pleased to host the Closing Ceremony at DevFest!  

The challenge: Alberta's Aging Oil and Gas Infrastructure.  "Alberta's Oil and Gas industry has collectively amassed ~90,000 inactive wells. While a subset have future potential and are subject to reactivation, the majority are candidates for abandonment."

In this session, we'll talk about culture hacking and how it is changing the way that solutions are created for the Oil and Gas industry.  We will then see some of the top solutions submitted for the data competition and the winner will be crowned!

sessions.title: Your Experience is User Experience
sessions.description: Ever find an edge case that breaks a design? Missing a style guide and a designer? As a developer, sometimes you’re left to design on the fly. In Your Experience is User Experience, learn tips and strategies on how to identify areas a design can be improved upon, how to come up with a functional and beautifully designed solution, and how to present it to your client.

sessions.title: How Google App Maker Helps a Non-Developer to... Develop
sessions.description: A sharing of my adventure in using Google App Maker to develop a complex workflow tool while starting out with no previous web app development experience

sessions.title: Immediate Rent
sessions.description: Would like to briefly talk about Immediate Rent project and discuss what Code and DEV stack we are using.

sessions.title: Up and Running with Progressive Web Apps
sessions.description:
This will be a workshop to get beginner level developers started with PWA. 
Will touch upon differences between web and pwa.
Then some core concepts like Service Workers, a few caching strategies and finally hit coding on an online IDE sycned with GitHub so that everyone is on the same page.
Will keep it stress free coding session, something similar to Qwiklabs.

sessions.title: A non-dev, in a dev world
sessions.description: As a leader and non- developer, it can be challenging to work with and manage technical experts. This presentation will highlight some of the humorous quirks of working with developers, and some suggestions for non-devs on how to work closely with developers. It is possible for devs and non-devs to collaborate closely and have a little fun at the same time!
